Description: The Flight into Egypt, with the Holy Family accompanied by angels. mid/late 1640s Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Giovanni Benedetto Castiglione
Published by: Giovanni Domenico de' Rossi
Bibliographic references: Bellini 1982 / L'Opera incisa di Giovanni Benedetto Castiglione (20.III)
Acquisition notes: The evidence on the verso of this sheet is contradictory. Although the initials HS are inscribed in pencil at center, the sheet presents in the lower left corner Philipe's blindstamp with no intials (probably washed out) and the 1870s BM Cracherode Collection stamp. Given the quality of the impression and the conditions of the sheet, characteristic more of Cracherode's collection than of Sloane's, precedence has been given to the evidence of a Cracherode provenance.
